  <div data-component="article-content">


            <p>We just got <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/gears-of-war-e-day-release-platform-skipping-ps5-rumour">another look at Gears of War: E-Day</a> and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/steampunk-rpg-clockwork-revolution-arrives-2027-as-an-xbox-console-exclusive">Clockwork Revolution at this evening's Xbox Games Showcase</a>. While <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/xboxs-state-of-decay-3-and-gears-of-war-e-day-heading-to-ps5-report-claims">many had assumed that Gears of War: E-Day specifically would be coming to PlayStation 5 as well</a> as part of Xbox's recent drive to release its game across multiple platforms, that is not the case.</p>
<p>But, it is not just that these games aren't coming to PlayStation consoles yet. It looks like they aren't coming to PS5 at all.</p>

<figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="Clockwork Revolution - The Heist | XBOX Games Showcase 2026" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/6B5NUd6B9I4?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
<span>Clockwork Revolution - The Heist | XBOX Games Showcase 2026</span>
<template>
<iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/6B5NUd6B9I4?autoplay=1" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/6B5NUd6B9I4?autoplay=1" title="Clockwork Revolution - The Heist | XBOX Games Showcase 2026">
